With their popular Music in the Zoo series not returning this summer, Twin Cities concert promoters Sue McLean & Associates are focusing their attention on other outdoor shows, including a big weekend pairing with blues-rocker Gary Clark Jr. and country-pop star Kelsea Ballerini at Plymouth's Hilde Amphitheater on July 29 and 30, respectively. Tickets for those Friday and Saturday night shows go on sale Friday at 10 a.m.  priced $60-$150, with options including a two-day pass for both concerts. Pre-sale access begins Tuesday. You've read your complimentary articles for this time period.
