  Already a subscriber? Log in here.  "We understand the Minnesota Zoo is focused on their animal collection and their own events, and there are no plans to bring back Music in the Zoo at this time," SMA president Patricia McLean said in a statement, which offered another consolation for Twin Cities concertgoers: Her company will also once again produce concerts at Canterbury Park. Stay tuned for details on the gigs to be held inside the horse track in Shakopee, which last summer included performances by Old Crow Medicine Show, Daughtry, En Vogue, Steve Earle and Robert Cray.  